data.title: Bridal Veil Falls, a waterfall located on Bridal Veil Creek in the Columbia River Gorge in Multnomah County, Oregon
authors: PICRYL - Public Domain Media Search Engine
data.meta_description:
Download Image of Bridal Veil Falls, a waterfall located on Bridal Veil Creek in the Columbia River Gorge in Multnomah County, Oregon. Free for commercial use, no attribution required.  The falls consists of two cascades in quick succession along angling rockfaces, so when there is a good amount of water the falls looks very much like its namesake. Many couples have their wedding invitations shipped to the nearby post office in the town of Bridal Veil in order to have the town's postmark applied to them.
Title, date and keywords based on information provided by the photographer.
Purchase; Carol M. Highsmith Photography, Inc.; 2018; (DLC/PP-2016:103-12)
Forms part of Carol M. Highsmith's America Project in the Carol M. Highsmith Archive.
